review_blob:
Gotta give props to these guys out of Ft Lauderdale. Being a native myself, I love what these guys are doing. This is a Pale Ale that deserves attention! Tricks you with tastes like a west coast IPA with its big hit of pine and settles nicely with its pale ale mode of operation. IPA lovers/hop heads like myself will be more than satisfied, and then some. Skip the aroma... Not much of a frothy head but when it hits the palate, you can't help but say "wooooow." It's a big piney hit that ends with that typical citrus smack. Medium body and great beer all around. Can't get enough! Will NOT dissapoint

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

My favorite Rye beer of all time... So my rating is a bit biased. Love everything about it. Rich copper in color. Aromas of deep, Rye malts. Taste is a quick hit of Rye with pretty big citrusy hops, 48 IBUs. One of the best if your a fan of Rye

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

A more unique IPA than most I've had. First tastes were very nutty and grassy; tasted almonds. Good malts, caramel was strong. Although they advertised it to be for a hop head, id say it's more PG13 on the hops. Good beer none the less. Not memorable but very drinkable 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Do these guys make a bad beer?! BOOM! HOPS! At 85 IBUs you either have a make it or break it hoppy beer and these guys did it right! Great IPA. Everything you want. Grapefruit hits you hard initially with the big hoppy finish. Finishes smooth yet chewy. Poured it from the 16oz tallboy can. Definite must drink for the hophead out there. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Oskar Blues Deviant Dales India Pale Ale

review_blob:
The hops in this porter are a great compliment otherwise I wouldn't score it as high. Chocolate on the nose and a rich, dark chocolate, velvety taste. Overall a pretty damn good porter. One of my go to's.

Well balanced hops. Spicy rye on the nose with deep, ruby/amber color. Fresh, grassy but chewy when it hits the mouth then quickly smacks you with the earthy Rye although I wish the Rye was a bit stronger. Overall great beer.
beer_name: Bear Republic Hop Rod Rye Ale
